28/08/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Authorities announced on Friday (26 August) that forensic experts finally identified the remains of the German pilot of the crashed Cypriot plane, 50-year Hans Juergen Merten, with the help of DNA testing and dental records. The Helios Boeing 737 went down in the mountains north of Athens two weeks, killing all 121 people on board. (Kathimerini - 27/08/05; ANA - 26/08/05) 
